QualitativeValue.name: greater
QualitativeValue.desc: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than the object.

QualitativeValue.name: equal
QualitativeValue.desc: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is equal to the object.

QualitativeValue.name: additionalProperty
QualitativeValue.desc:
A property-value pair representing an additional characteristics of the entitity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there is no matching property in schema.org.

Note: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. http://schema.org/width, http://schema.org/color, http://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.

QualitativeValue.name: lesser
QualitativeValue.desc: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than the object.

QualitativeValue.name: valueReference
QualitativeValue.desc: A pointer to a secondary value that provides additional information on the original value, e.g. a reference temperature.

QualitativeValue.name: nonEqual
QualitativeValue.desc: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is not equal to the object.

QualitativeValue.name: lesserOrEqual
QualitativeValue.desc: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than or equal to the object.

QualitativeValue.name: greaterOrEqual
QualitativeValue.desc: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than or equal to the object.
